\date{2026-03-10}
\date{2026-03-17}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\meta{external}{https://github.com/samtoth/agda-synthetic-categories/pull/63}
\title{More closure properties of localisations}
\tag{changelog}
\import{stt-macros}

\p{
We show a slew of closure properties of
[localisations](Modalities.Instances.Localisation) and
[nullifications](Modalities.Instances.Nullification). As an application, these
closure properties will help us construct
[simplicial types](Synthetic.Categories.Simplicial) and
[synthetic categories](stt-????).
}

\p{
For localisations/reflective subuniverses we show closure under retracts, and
formation of pullbacks, fibres, equalisers, sequential limits, retract types,
equivalence types, quasiidempotent maps, and universes of retracts. We also show that
propositions are local at families of maps whose domains are inhabited.
}

\p{
While most of these results appear in \citek{CORS20}, closure under forming
quasiidempotent maps and the universe of retracts do not to our knowledge appear in
the literature, and are due to [[egbertrijke]]. We show that the type of
quasiidempotent maps
[can be presented as a pullback over the underlying type](fre-9875), and from
pullback closure obtain that it is itself local. From closure under formation of
quasiidempotent maps we use the splitting construction of Shulman
\citek{shulman-idempotents-2017} to obtain that the universe of retracts of a local
type is also local.
}

\p{
For nullifications we additionally show that universes of null types at families of
propositions are themselves null at that family of propositions, following
\citet{Thm 3.11}{RSS2020}. We extend this result to subuniverses that are closed
under mapping out of the given family of propositions.
}

\p{
As corollaries, we obtain that the universe of
[simplicial](Synthetic.Categories.Simplicial)/[disjunctive](Synthetic.Categories.Disjunctive)
types is itself simplicial/disjunctive, and that the type of
[precategories](Synthetic.Categories.Precategories) is simplicial. We
also obtain that propositions are [Segal](stt-00AI).
}

\p{
In addition to the above we add
[biinvertible maps](Foundations.BiinvertibleMap),
[surjections](Foundations.Surjection), [the canonical image](fre-2145)
and some basic properties of images, the
[6-for-2 property of equivalences](Foundations.6for2), and [small types](Core.Small).
We formalise that small types are closed under retracts using the splitting
construction, and we formalise the [type theoretic replacement theorem](fre-2143)
\citet{Thm 4.6}{rijke-2017} using [the modified join construction](stt-008G). We also
show that
[maps whose action on identifications have a section are embeddings](fre-0012), and
that [retracts are closed under taking actions on identifications](fre-2138).
}

